00:16.980 --> 00:18.389
Have you got a fire extinguisher?

00:18.390 --> 00:20.199
-A f...?
-For putting out fires.

00:20.200 --> 00:21.959
I've got one in the car,
but I may need something bigger.

00:21.960 --> 00:24.519
There's a fella round the corner
reckoning to set fire to himself!

00:24.520 --> 00:26.940
Thank you, we're on top of that.
How much for these?

00:30.870 --> 00:32.829
Nice glasses.

00:32.830 --> 00:35.439
Well, he can send himself to
paradise - that's his choice -

00:35.440 --> 00:38.709
but he's not
taking my eyebrows with him.

00:38.710 --> 00:41.629
Oh, what, you think
I give a toss about what you do?

00:41.630 --> 00:44.119
You're just bloody scum,
you're like pigs, like animals!

00:44.120 --> 00:46.159
-Do we know his name?
-Liam Hughes.

00:46.160 --> 00:48.439
23.
Unemployed. Smackhead.

00:48.440 --> 00:50.779
-What's he upset about?
-His ex.

00:50.780 --> 00:53.579
-His ex.
-She finished with him three days ago,

00:53.580 --> 00:55.930
now she's sleeping
with his best bud.

00:56.310 --> 00:58.419
We've got a high-ranking
highly trained

00:58.420 --> 01:01.579
specialist expert police negotiator
on his way over from Wakefield.

01:01.580 --> 01:03.029
ETA?

01:03.030 --> 01:05.760
Basically it's you and me, kid.

01:07.150 --> 01:09.239
Go and close down the comedy
department.

01:09.240 --> 01:11.149
The one and only...
human barbecue!

01:11.150 --> 01:13.719
You come any closer and
I'm setting meself off, all right!

01:13.720 --> 01:15.029
What's happened, Liam?

01:15.030 --> 01:16.439
I don't know why
you've brought that.

01:16.440 --> 01:18.349
If you accidentally
fireball yourself...

01:18.350 --> 01:21.200
You're going to get foamed,
and believe you me,
it's not a good look.

01:23.770 --> 01:25.699
How's it all come to this then, lad?

01:25.700 --> 01:27.359
I've been humiliated.

01:27.360 --> 01:28.709
Humiliated?

01:28.710 --> 01:31.620
I don't want to talk about it
all right? OK.

01:32.850 --> 01:35.719
You know, actions speak
louder than words.

01:35.720 --> 01:38.270
OK. Can I just say this though,
Liam?

01:38.580 --> 01:40.889
The lighter's making me nervous.

01:40.890 --> 01:43.129
You've had a lot to drink
and you've got the shakes

01:43.130 --> 01:45.859
and you might press it without intending
to, and I'd like you to put it down.

01:45.860 --> 01:47.469
Leave me alone,
you stupid bitch.

01:47.470 --> 01:48.909
You're upset,
I understand that.

01:48.910 --> 01:51.389
The point I'm making is
that with all these fumes...

01:51.390 --> 01:53.199
frankly, I don't know how
you're staying conscious -

01:53.200 --> 01:55.489
you could go up any second
whether you intend to or not,

01:55.490 --> 01:57.819
and once you go up,
you won't just go up a bit,

01:57.820 --> 02:00.999
you'll go up a lot, and the
other big thing to say is, it hurts.

02:01.000 --> 02:03.549
Three seconds in
and you'll be screaming at me

02:03.550 --> 02:06.259
seven seconds in and you'll
be begging me to shoot you.

02:06.260 --> 02:08.219
<i>I've a negotiator
on his way to you,</i>

02:08.220 --> 02:10.579
<i>-but he's stuck in traffic.</i>
-OK.

02:10.580 --> 02:13.970
<i>He says the big thing is to keep the
subject engaged in conversation.</i>

02:14.380 --> 02:16.189
Yeah, I think we've got that
covered.

02:16.190 --> 02:17.769
I'm Catherine, by the way.

02:17.770 --> 02:20.589
I'm 47, I'm divorced,
I live with my sister

02:20.590 --> 02:22.549
who's a recovering
heroin addict.

02:22.550 --> 02:24.269
I have two grown-up children.
One dead,

02:24.270 --> 02:26.680
one who doesn't speak to me,
and a grandson. So...

02:27.780 --> 02:30.439
Why? Why doesn't he speak to you?

02:30.440 --> 02:32.710
It's complicated.
Let's talk about you.

02:45.120 --> 02:48.220
Happy Valley
Season 1 - Episode 01

02:51.120 --> 02:54.100
Subtitles by Red Bee Media Ltd
